Introduction and overview
The awarding of services by contracting authorities is of great importance both for the state and for the economy.
The State has the task of using the public resources as economically and economically as possible and ensuring a fair and regulated competition.
In The European Union (EU), the awarding of services by contracting contracting entities is an important part of the creation of a single economic area.
In order to ensure a largely unlimited competition also cross-border, contracting authorities have to comply with the requirements of the EU for their award-granted contracts.
To this end, EU member states have the right to transfer and apply the EU's national law in national law.
This has already happened in the Czech Republic as well as in Germany.
