Recommendations Recommendations Recommendations Recommendations Recommendations
The nku and the brh evaluate the implementation of EU standards in principle positive.
The widespread acceptance in practice has confirmed that the EU commandments of competition, equal treatment and transparency are a suitable basis for the awarding of construction works within the European Union.
The Supranational model implemented in the European Union can also be used as a basis for similar projects to enable and promote cross-border competition.
In view of the enormous material and cost-effective damage potential through manipulation and corruption in the awarding of construction works, both audit have called for the bauverwaltungen in their countries to continue their actions against corruption and manipulation and, if necessary still to improve.
In particular, the organisation and application procedures of the procurement procedures should be continuously investigated for vulnerabilities and risks in order to identify action and to initiate appropriate countermeasures.
The comparison of the contracts in both countries suggests that the share of open procedures in the Czech Republic should be increased, as open procedures offer a wider space for competition and can significantly reduce the risk of loss.
A stronger division of construction works can also have a beneficial impact on the production of goods, provided that a greater competition is achieved with a higher number of bidders.
